on EUR/JPY, DAX Index and Dow Jones Index,

80
00:07:18,330 --> 00:07:26,620
my favorite instruments to scalp:

81
00:07:26,620 --> 00:07:43,789
So, what’s the psychology behind this trading
technique? Well, we try to take advantage

82
00:07:43,789 --> 00:07:49,899
of novice traders, shorting the market below
50 EMA. Think about it. We are practically

83
00:07:49,899 --> 00:07:55,150
waiting for the price to close below the 50
EMA. But other traders, when they see the

84
00:07:55,150 --> 00:08:00,539
price closing below the 50 EMA, they immediately
short the market. They don’t care about

85
00:08:00,539 --> 00:08:05,889
the general trend, they see the price below
50 EMA and enter short. That’s why we wait

86
00:08:05,889 --> 00:08:11,860
for the price to return above the 50 EMA.
We want to have trapped traders below us,

87
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:17,639
to fuel our long positions. Where are the
stops of the traders shorting below the 50

88
00:08:17,639 --> 00:08:23,710
EMA? You guessed it, above the 50 EMA. When
the price returns above the moving average,

89
00:08:23,710 --> 00:08:28,699
our scalping trade gets an extra boost from
the stop of trapped traders.

90
00:08:28,699 --> 00:08:35,370
Now, here are some important observations:
Scalping can easily turn to gambling. Excited

91
00:08:35,370 --> 00:08:41,620
traders on a winning streak will abandon their
own rules in pursuit of fast money. If it

92
00:08:41,620 --> 00:08:47,350
happens once, it can easily happen again.
Being impulsive is one of the most undesirable

93
00:08:47,350 --> 00:08:53,140
traits for forex scalping. That’s why, try
to improve your discipline and self-control

94
00:08:53,140 --> 00:08:58,250
before attempting scalping.
Second, scalping is one of those trading methods

95
00:08:58,250 --> 00:09:04,910
that are often performed with bad risk reward
ratio. Trader will often risk 100 pips just

96
00:09:04,910 --> 00:09:10,770
for the possibility of gaining 1 or 2. Market
provides plenty of opportunity to enter high

97
00:09:10,770 --> 00:09:16,820
probability setups that can make this reward
sustainable. Unfortunately this trading style

98
00:09:16,820 --> 00:09:22,990
also means that days and weeks of profit can
be wiped out with relative ease. Few bad trades

99
00:09:22,990 --> 00:09:28,180
in a row can therefore produce substantial
losses. That’s why when I’m scalping I’m

100
00:09:28,180 --> 00:09:37,500
not risking more than 0.5% of my total balance.
Not 5%, 0.5%.so, if you have 5.000 dollars

101
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:44,000
in your account, for example, if you scalp,
risk at most 25 dollars per trade.

102
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:50,260
My third recommendation, lower you lot sizes.
Small lots help you keep losses down until

103
00:09:50,260 --> 00:09:53,760
your trading improves and is consistently
proﬁtable. The smaller the forex lot size,

104
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:58,071
the lower the risk.
Also, don’t neglect the trading costs. Scalping

105
00:09:58,071 --> 00:10:04,550
requires frequent trading almost by definition.
Frequent trading also means frequent and substantial

106
00:10:04,550 --> 00:10:10,650
position entry costs. Small difference in
spread between a great broker and good broker

107
00:10:10,650 --> 00:10:16,020
may be the difference between a consistently
winning strategy and a consistently losing

108
